=== Other expenditures ===
The Public Works Department spent $1 million on supplies and services for maintaining city streets.<ref>When goods or services are received, the amount to be paid is debited to the expenditure account and credited to a liability (payable) account. Hay, p. 63. Transactions involving purchase orders involve [[encumbrance]] accounting, requiring a more complex transaction than the simplified example shown here.</ref>
